<AbstractNarration>AST-0520740/Henry, Tennessee State University&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Three new 0.8 m automated photoelectric telescopes will be obtained for high-precision photometry of planetary-candidate target stars in the northern and southern hemispheres. The telescopes will complement high-resolution Doppler spectroscopy to separate out true exoplanet candidates from stellar magnetic variations that can mimic periodic Doppler effects.</AbstractNarration>
